quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  55,26,All that is upon it passes away
  55,27,"And there remains the Face of thy Lord, Possessed of Majesty and Bounty"
  55,28,So which of your Lord’s boons do you two deny
  55,29,"Those in the heavens and on the earth entreat Him: every day He is upon a task"
  55,30,So which of your Lord’s boons do you two deny
  55,31,We shall have leisure for you both
  55,32,weighty ones
  55,33,So which of your Lord’s boons do you two deny
  55,34,"O company of jinn and men, if you are able to pass beyond the regions of the heavens and the earth, then pass, you shall not pass, save by a warrant"
  55,35,So which of your Lord’s boons do you two deny
  55,36,"A flash of fire and molten brass shall be sent against you, and you shall not prevail"
  55,37,So which of your Lord’s boons do you two deny
  55,38,When the sky shall be rent asunder and when it shall turn ruddy like hide
  55,39,So which of your Lord’s boons do you two deny
  55,40,On that Day no man shall be questioned as to his sin; nor shall any jinn
  55,41,So which of your Lord’s boons do you two deny
  55,42,The guilty shall be known by their marks; and they shall be seized by the forelocks and by the feet
  55,43,So which of your Lord’s boons do you two deny
  55,44,This is Hell that the guilty deny
  55,45,"to and fro shall they pass, between it and boiling waters"